snippet.textDisplay:
I "say" my problem with myself is that I have no ambition.
That I hate myself because I never put out the effort to go after anything.


But that's not really why I hate myself. I hate myself because I know that, even though there ARE goals out there that do spark my interest, deep down inside, I just don't WANT to go after them. Life and the limited time we have in it makes me FEEL like I have to achieve these goals, and I know that I could do them if I put my mind towards them, but when it comes down to doing things, I just default to playing video games or watching Youtube and other passive hobbies whenever I'm not doing school work. Because those don't require effort, those hobbies don't FEEL like work. Basically, I don't like working on things that I don't have to do, and any ambitious goals i might have FEEL like work when I go to do them, because they ARE work (that's what makes them goals to be achieved in the first place), so I opt to just do "relaxing" instead. Call it laziness; you're probably right.


In any case, I hate myself because on one hand, I feel like i'm wasting my one opportunity of living a life worth living by being passive.
But on the other hand, I know for a fact I don't actively WANT to waste time and effort on pointless "goals" in my freetime, when I could be relaxing instead. If I did WANT to do those things, it wouldn't even be a question. You shouldn't have to motivate or convince yourself to do something if you truly WANT to do it. Circling back to the only issue there is I feel like a degenerate loser when all I do each day is play games and watch Youtube, all the while knowing that people like Mark and Ethan are out there, being awesome, accomplishing goals, and living their lives to the fullest.


So I dont hate myself for having no ambition
I dont even hate myself because I desperately WANT to have ambition, but I know I don't.
I hate myself because I view everything I do in life as pointless, and its killing me, no matter which end of the decision I land on.


I think my goals are pointless wastes of time (let's say making a Youtube channel as just one of many examples)
I think my "relaxing" hobbies like games and watching Youtube are pointless wastes of time
And I actively dislike engineering work, but it's the only career path I have lined up and see myself doing to be successful in the future. That being said, engineering work isn't exactly something I passionately want to dedicate my life to, just something to get the bills paid.
Which in essence, makes me feel like everything I learn is a pointless waste of time as far as positively advancing my life goes.


When im working im wasting my life doing something i don't like doing
When im relaxing i'm wasting my life by not pursuing more ambitious goals
When i pursue more ambitious goals, im wasting my life because they're all actually childish goals that are never going to amount to anything because i don't have the time, dedication, effort, or natural talent to turn any of them into anything id ever be proud of doing. (Not without compromising my one Engineering gameplan in life that is)


The gut reaction there is to say "you'll never know if you don't try"
But if I go out and "try", the time and effort that would be taking away from my engineering degree could kill my chance at a comfortable life, all for some things I've never done before but felt like trying because "they seemed cool", when in actuality they all require tons of luck and skill to ever be successful at in the first place.
I might hate my life and myself for the next 2 years until I graduate, but...


You know, I'm just gonna leave this rambling as is.
IF you've read this far, that means you're compassionate, so hey, you're pretty cool. But I dont know, I just put this here because, one day, this video's gonna be deleted anyways.


I'm not looking for advice, and I hate when people pity me (Seems to happen a lot), but i suppose I wouldnt have written this bit if there wasn't some part insde me that's desperately calling out for some sort of attention, help or assurance in some way, so I'll tell you what:
Pile all that on top of the fact that Im miserable about hating college kid culture, yet still really wanting to have friends to no avail, and shit sucks.


I'm gonna end this on a simple ... "I don't know"
And again, thanks if you read this far. Sorry for the massive mood-killer.
